reviews.review_text:
Nice TLEO Good show, pretty good recording, Jerry's voice has that nice raspy sound to it, and TLEO smokes
4 stars

china-rider nice tasty and long transition into rider. the rider is also tasty, not 'blistering' but tasty. No 'extra guitar break in between 'sun gonna shine' and 'wish I were a headlight...'but a nice tasty and long(but not blistering, its tasty) guitar break before final chorus. overall nice tasty and long version at 14 minutes. for blistering versions of the era check out ALL the versions from the short winter 81 tour, cleveland , msg etc. bottom line this is one of the best of 82.

nice job on recording too. i havent checked out the SBD as this is a 'matrix' most SBD's of 81/82 (not all) are problematic with 'hot' vocals and keyboards, imperfect mixes, low /no bass etc
